0:15:51.827 --> 0:15:53.237
I know. Isn't it great?

0:15:53.412 --> 0:15:55.752
No! I'm gonna be totally sick.

0:15:55.914 --> 0:15:58.714
It's the California current, dude.
It's got some gnarly chop.

0:15:58.876 --> 0:16:00.376
Surf's up, dude!

0:16:01.920 --> 0:16:04.380
Hey, dude, if you're gonna hurl,
just do me a solid...

0:16:04.548 --> 0:16:07.588
Head to the back of the shell, lean out,
and go for distance.

0:16:07.759 --> 0:16:09.759
We call that "feeding the fishes."

0:16:09.928 --> 0:16:11.098
Correctamundo, squirt!

0:16:11.263 --> 0:16:15.183
And now we're looking for my parents
at the brooch of the Atlantic? Or the--

0:16:15.350 --> 0:16:16.940
-the Jewel of morro bay, California.
-Exactly!

0:16:17.060 --> 0:16:18.850
How are you gonna find your parents?

0:16:19.021 --> 0:16:20.811
Do you remember what they look like?

0:16:20.939 --> 0:16:22.769
I'm a bit new to the memory thing,
so I can't say for sure...

0:16:22.858 --> 0:16:26.568
But something tells me they were
mostly blue, with s-- maybe yellow.

0:16:26.737 --> 0:16:27.397
That sounds right.

0:16:27.571 --> 0:16:31.161
Also I'm pretty sure I'm gonna know
them when I see them. We're family.

0:16:31.283 --> 0:16:34.043
By the way crossing the ocean
is the kind of thing you should...

0:16:34.203 --> 0:16:36.203
Only do once. One time!

0:16:36.371 --> 0:16:38.791
Morro bay, California's
coming up, dudes.

0:16:39.917 --> 0:16:42.087
Whoo-hoo! Let's find my family.

0:16:42.252 --> 0:16:43.422
Go! Go! Go, go, go.

0:16:43.587 --> 0:16:45.877
-Just go, dad.
-Don't push me, Nemo.

0:16:51.386 --> 0:16:54.756
So long, little blue!
Hope you find your parents.

0:16:54.932 --> 0:16:56.772
And good luck "feeding the fishes."

0:16:58.060 --> 0:16:59.770
Too late. Already fed.

0:17:00.145 --> 0:17:01.145
Oh.

0:17:05.317 --> 0:17:08.607
This feels familiar. Mom! Dad!

0:17:08.779 --> 0:17:10.529
No. Dory! Dory! Wait! Wait.

0:17:11.281 --> 0:17:13.121
Mom! Dad!

0:17:13.283 --> 0:17:15.873
Stop yelling for a second.
Do you really think your parents...

0:17:15.953 --> 0:17:18.413
Are just gonna be floating around here
waiting for you?

0:17:18.580 --> 0:17:21.830
Well, I don't know, but there's only
one way to find out. Mom! Dad!

0:17:22.000 --> 0:17:24.630
-Yell louder, dory.
-Mom! Dad!

0:17:24.795 --> 0:17:26.505
-Sh!
-What was that?

0:17:27.130 --> 0:17:31.930
Wait. I've heard that before.
I remember someone saying, "sh."

0:17:32.094 --> 0:17:34.054
Yes, well done. That was me.
One minute ago.

0:17:34.137 --> 0:17:34.797
Sh!

0:17:36.765 --> 0:17:39.845
Please. Have you seen
my mommy and daddy?

0:17:40.018 --> 0:17:42.308
Their names are Jenny and Charlie.

0:17:42.354 --> 0:17:43.024
Sh!

0:17:45.148 --> 0:17:47.068
Jenny and Charlie.

0:17:47.192 --> 0:17:48.032
What? Jenny and what?

0:17:48.110 --> 0:17:51.030
Those are their names!
My parents are Jenny and Charlie!

0:17:51.196 --> 0:17:52.776
-Dory, wait!
-Jenny!

0:17:52.823 --> 0:17:55.163
Can't we just take a moment
to come up with a plan?

0:17:55.325 --> 0:17:57.615
-Jenny! Charlie!
-Sh!

0:17:57.786 --> 0:17:59.996
-Are you crazy?
-Sorry, she's a little excited.

0:18:00.163 --> 0:18:02.873
-Jenny! Charlie!
-Dory, stop yelling for a second.

0:18:03.000 --> 0:18:05.670
It's not a good idea
to come into a new neighborhood...

0:18:05.836 --> 0:18:08.206
And call this much attention to yourself.

0:18:08.380 --> 0:18:11.340
You don't understand. I remembered
my parent's names! Jenny! Charlie!

0:18:11.508 --> 0:18:15.178
These crabs are locals and i
get the feeling they're shushing...

0:18:15.345 --> 0:18:18.005
Us for a reason. You might wake up
something dangerous.

0:18:18.140 --> 0:18:20.230
Are you talking about like
something with one big eye...

0:18:20.392 --> 0:18:21.272
Tentacles, and a snappy thing?

0:18:21.393 --> 0:18:24.023
Well, that's very specific,
but something like that, yes.

0:18:24.188 --> 0:18:26.188
You just in general don't want to--

0:18:28.734 --> 0:18:31.744
oh my goodness. Okay.

0:18:31.904 --> 0:18:36.374
There's a mistake. We're backing away.
Let us live and we will--

0:18:36.491 --> 0:18:41.041
we'll worship you. We'll build a--
do you like a monument?

0:18:48.921 --> 0:18:53.471
Oh! Ooh! Whoa! Swim for your life!

0:19:10.901 --> 0:19:12.531
-Nemo!
-Nemo!

0:19:14.029 --> 0:19:14.489
Dad!

0:19:14.613 --> 0:19:15.703
-Nemo!
-Dad!

0:19:21.912 --> 0:19:22.912
No!

0:19:23.080 --> 0:19:25.420
Nemo, hold on to me and don't let go!

0:19:26.250 --> 0:19:27.080
Dad!

0:19:27.543 --> 0:19:28.423
No, no! No!

0:19:34.800 --> 0:19:37.430
Dory! Dory, slow down!
We're not being chased anymore.

0:19:37.594 --> 0:19:38.434
Are you sure?

0:19:42.432 --> 0:19:45.602
Jenny and Charlie. Jenny and Charlie!

0:19:46.395 --> 0:19:49.275
I just remembered their names!
We have to keep going. We're so close.

0:19:49.439 --> 0:19:50.569
-Huh?
-Nemo, are you hurt?

0:19:50.691 --> 0:19:54.281
Oh my goodness! Nemo!
Are you okay? What happened?

0:19:54.444 --> 0:19:56.114
-Not now, dory. Please!
-Oh no.

0:19:56.280 --> 0:19:58.620
-Nemo. Oh no. Oh no.
-I'm okay.

0:19:58.782 --> 0:20:00.742
Oh, Nemo. I'm sorry. Okay. I'm sorry.

0:20:02.119 --> 0:20:04.119
Oh my goodness! Nemo, are you okay?

0:20:04.288 --> 0:20:06.248
I said, "not now." You've done enough.

0:20:06.415 --> 0:20:11.675
I have? Oh no. But I can fix it.
I can. I'll go get help.

0:20:11.837 --> 0:20:14.297
You know what you can do, dory?
You can go wait over there.

0:20:14.464 --> 0:20:18.054
Go wait over there and forget.
It's what you do best.

0:20:20.596 --> 0:20:23.636
You're right. I don't know why I thought
i could do this.

0:20:23.807 --> 0:20:28.187
Find my family. I can't do this.
I'm so sorry. I'll fix it.

0:20:28.353 --> 0:20:30.113
-I'm okay.
-Well, I'm gonna get help. Okay?

0:20:30.272 --> 0:20:34.322
Okay? I can do that. I'll be--
it'll be all right, Nemo.

0:20:37.446 --> 0:20:39.816
Hello? Someone? Hello?

0:20:39.990 --> 0:20:42.870
Anyone? Hello? Anyone?

0:20:43.035 --> 0:20:44.495
Hello.

0:20:45.662 --> 0:20:48.042
-Hello?
-I'm sigourney Weaver.

0:20:48.207 --> 0:20:51.037
Oh. Hi, sigourney. I need your help.

0:20:51.168 --> 0:20:53.168
Won't you please join us...

0:20:53.295 --> 0:20:54.715
Oh. Great, great, great.

0:20:54.880 --> 0:20:58.130
As we explore the wonders
of the pacific ocean...

0:20:58.300 --> 0:21:01.550
And the amazing life it holds within.

0:21:01.720 --> 0:21:03.890
Witness the majesty
of the beluga whale.

0:21:04.056 --> 0:21:05.516
Sigourney Weaver, where are you?

0:21:05.641 --> 0:21:06.681
Dory! There you are!

0:21:06.850 --> 0:21:09.520
Guys! I found help. Sigourney Weaver's
gonna tell us where we are.

0:21:09.686 --> 0:21:10.846
Look out!

0:21:11.021 --> 0:21:13.691
-Oh, look at this!
-No respect for ocean life.

0:21:13.815 --> 0:21:16.025
-Marlin! Nemo!
-Dory!

0:21:16.151 --> 0:21:17.241
No, no, no. Not again! Not again!

0:21:17.361 --> 0:21:18.901
Let's take her inside
and see how she does.

0:21:21.865 --> 0:21:22.525
Dory! Dory!

0:21:22.699 --> 0:21:26.369
Don't worry, dory! Stay calm.
We'll come find you!

0:21:26.537 --> 0:21:29.037
And welcome to
the marine life institute...

0:21:29.206 --> 0:21:32.826
Where we believe in rescue,
rehabilitation and release.

0:21:35.671 --> 0:21:37.211
Marlin? Nemo?

0:21:42.845 --> 0:21:45.355
Hello? Hello? Can you help me?

0:21:45.514 --> 0:21:46.894
Me help you?

0:21:55.315 --> 0:21:57.525
Huh? What's happening? Help?

0:21:57.693 --> 0:21:58.863
Looks like we're done here.

0:21:59.027 --> 0:22:01.277
Dude, cut it out. You're a scientist.
We talked about this.

0:22:01.446 --> 0:22:02.776
Oh, come on. It's funny.

0:22:08.912 --> 0:22:14.042
Oh boy. Okay. This is-- I'll be fine,
i just need to find a way out and...

0:22:23.135 --> 0:22:26.105
If I could just-- get a hold of yourself,
get a hold of yourself.

0:22:26.263 --> 0:22:29.103
You'll be fine, everything's fine,
think positively.

0:22:29.266 --> 0:22:31.016
-Hey, you.
-Oh.

0:22:31.143 --> 0:22:31.983
Spinner.

0:22:32.144 --> 0:22:34.604
Oh, thank goodness. Hi, I'm dory. I'm--

0:22:34.730 --> 0:22:36.650
name's Hank. How sick are you?

0:22:36.815 --> 0:22:37.935
Sick? I'm sick?

0:22:38.108 --> 0:22:39.108
Why else would you be in quarantine?

0:22:39.276 --> 0:22:41.236
Oh no! How long do I have?
I have to find my family.

0:22:41.361 --> 0:22:43.991
All right. Now don't get hysterical--
uh-oh. Not good.

0:22:44.156 --> 0:22:46.776
What? What is it? What happened?
What's that?

0:22:46.950 --> 0:22:48.490
That there is bad news.

0:22:48.785 --> 0:22:51.995
It's a transport tag for fish
who can't cut it inside the institute.

0:22:52.164 --> 0:22:55.294
They get transferred to permanent digs.
An aquarium.

0:22:55.459 --> 0:22:57.039
In Cleveland.

0:22:57.628 --> 0:23:02.338
Fish in here, go back in the ocean.
Cleveland fish, stay there forever.

0:23:02.758 --> 0:23:05.088
Cleveland? No!
I can't go to the Cleveland.

0:23:05.260 --> 0:23:08.100
I have to get to the Jewel of morro bay,
California and find my family.

0:23:08.263 --> 0:23:10.103
That's this place.
The marine life institute.

0:23:10.224 --> 0:23:13.024
The Jewel of morro bay, California.
You're here.

0:23:13.810 --> 0:23:16.810
You mean I'm from here? My parents
are here. I have to get to them.

0:23:16.980 --> 0:23:18.190
So what exhibit are you from?

0:23:18.357 --> 0:23:21.317
Wait. I'm from an exhibit? Which one?
I have to get there.

0:23:21.485 --> 0:23:23.615
Hmm. That's a hard one, kid.

0:23:23.779 --> 0:23:27.949
Unless... nah.
Never work. It's too crazy.

0:23:28.075 --> 0:23:30.125
What do you mean? Just tell me.
I'm okay with crazy.

0:23:30.244 --> 0:23:33.294
You know, I could see that?
Well, there's one thing I can think of...

0:23:33.455 --> 0:23:36.365
To help you get to your family.
If I just take--

0:23:36.542 --> 0:23:39.792
yes! Great idea. You take me
to find them. Why didn't I think of that?

0:23:39.962 --> 0:23:42.842
No, no, no. If I just take your tag...

0:23:43.006 --> 0:23:46.676
I can take your place on the transport
truck then you can go back inside...

0:23:46.844 --> 0:23:50.014
And find your family. All you have to do
is give me the tag.

0:23:50.180 --> 0:23:52.220
What tag? There's a tag on my fin!

0:23:52.349 --> 0:23:54.809
How could you forget you have a tag
on your fin?

0:23:54.935 --> 0:23:58.865
Oh no. I'm sorry. I-- I suffer from
short-term memory loss.

0:23:59.690 --> 0:24:01.270
You don't remember
what we were talking about?

0:24:01.400 --> 0:24:04.070
Mm-mm. Not a clue.
What were we talking about?

0:24:04.194 --> 0:24:07.034
You were about to give me your tag.

0:24:07.197 --> 0:24:09.317
Well, I kind of like my tag.
Why do you want it?

0:24:09.449 --> 0:24:10.369
So I can go to--

0:24:11.785 --> 0:24:13.495
so I can go to Cleveland.

0:24:13.662 --> 0:24:16.002
Cleveland? I hear good things about
Cleveland. Why do you want to go?

0:24:16.123 --> 0:24:18.333
Because if I stay here I'm gonna get
released back to the ocean.

0:24:18.500 --> 0:24:20.670
And I have extremely
unpleasant memories of that place.

0:24:22.337 --> 0:24:24.417
I just want to live in a glass box alone.

0:24:24.590 --> 0:24:27.220
That's all I want. So give me your tag!

0:24:27.384 --> 0:24:28.724
Hey, man, don't touch my tag!

0:24:31.889 --> 0:24:32.679
Look...

0:24:39.062 --> 0:24:42.072
I don't work here. It's not like
i have a map of this place.

0:24:42.232 --> 0:24:43.442
A map! Good idea.

0:24:43.609 --> 0:24:46.649
You take me to the map, I figure out
where my parents are. Oh boy.

0:24:47.613 --> 0:24:51.283
All right. If I get you to your family
will you give me--

0:24:51.408 --> 0:24:55.038
I don't have much. I--
how about if I give you this tag?

0:24:55.412 --> 0:24:56.502
Great idea.

0:25:03.795 --> 0:25:05.795
Are you absolutely sure
that's what I said?

0:25:05.964 --> 0:25:08.764
"Go wait over there and forget.
That's what you do best."

0:25:08.926 --> 0:25:09.926
-Yeah, dad.
-I said that?

0:25:10.093 --> 0:25:11.933
You said that,
dory swam to the surface,

0:25:11.970 --> 0:25:13.260
and she got taken by some--

0:25:13.430 --> 0:25:14.560
all right, I don't want to hear
the whole story again.

0:25:14.723 --> 0:25:17.933
I was just asking about the one part
because, look, if I said that--

0:25:18.101 --> 0:25:21.941
I'm not positive I did. It's actually
a compliment because...

0:25:22.105 --> 0:25:25.105
I asked her to wait and I said,
"it's what you do best."

0:25:25.275 --> 0:25:28.275
So i-- oh, it's my fault!

0:25:28.445 --> 0:25:32.275
It's all my fault she got kidnapped
and taken into whatever this place is.

0:25:32.449 --> 0:25:34.079
What if it's a restaurant?

0:25:34.243 --> 0:25:36.583
Oy! You two! Shut it!

0:25:36.745 --> 0:25:40.575
Yeah, we're trying to sleep!
You interrupted my favorite dream!

0:25:40.749 --> 0:25:42.459
Is that the one about you
laying on this rock?

0:25:42.626 --> 0:25:44.956
-Yeah.
-Oh, that is a good one.

0:25:45.128 --> 0:25:46.798
-Oh yeah, isn't it? Yeah.
-It's one of my favorites.

0:25:46.964 --> 0:25:49.134
-Excuse us. Hello! We're trying to--
-son! Son.

0:25:49.299 --> 0:25:51.799
Those are sea lions.
They are natural predators.

0:25:51.969 --> 0:25:53.009
They could pounce at any moment.

0:25:55.055 --> 0:25:56.765
They don't look very pouncy.

0:25:56.932 --> 0:25:58.482
That's what they want you to think.

0:25:58.642 --> 0:26:01.312
Just get behind me
and let me do the talking.

0:26:01.478 --> 0:26:04.938
Excuse me, we're worried
about our friend. Is that a restaurant?

0:26:06.358 --> 0:26:09.818
Mate, it's not a restaurant.
Your friend is okay.

0:26:09.987 --> 0:26:12.107
-She is?
-It's a fish hospital.

0:26:12.281 --> 0:26:16.531
Sigourney Weaver says she'll be
rescued, rehabilitated, and released.

0:26:16.702 --> 0:26:18.702
She'll be in and out in a jiff.
We should know.

0:26:18.871 --> 0:26:20.461
-Nasal parasite.
-Anemia.

0:26:20.622 --> 0:26:22.212
All fixed up and sent on our way.

0:26:22.332 --> 0:26:24.422
Oh thank goodness.

0:26:24.543 --> 0:26:27.553
Sure, that's all right.
Don't you worry ab--

0:26:28.630 --> 0:26:30.800
-Gerald, get off the rock!
-Shove off, Gerald! Come on. Off! Off!

0:26:30.966 --> 0:26:34.836
-Get off! Now you know better! Off!
-Off! Off! Off! Off!

0:26:35.012 --> 0:26:39.852
Don't you worry about a thing.
That place is the marine life institute.

0:26:40.017 --> 0:26:42.097
The Jewel of morro bay, California.

0:26:42.227 --> 0:26:46.357
She was right. It looks like
dory can do something besides forget.

0:26:46.523 --> 0:26:48.323
Thank you, Nemo. Thank you for that.

0:26:48.483 --> 0:26:50.533
So how are we gonna get inside?

0:26:50.652 --> 0:26:52.202
Wait. You want to get inside mli?

0:26:52.362 --> 0:26:55.032
Desperately. Our friend is in there.
Lost, alone.

0:26:55.199 --> 0:26:57.369
She's scared.
She'll have no idea what to do.

0:26:57.534 --> 0:27:00.584
Oh, we know a way.

0:27:00.704 --> 0:27:04.424
-You do?
-Ooo-roo. Ooo-roo-roo. Ooo-roo.

0:27:04.541 --> 0:27:05.881
-What are they doing?
-I don't know. It sounds bad.

0:27:08.545 --> 0:27:10.205
-Are we there yet?
-Sh. Keep it down!

0:27:10.672 --> 0:27:14.472
Hank., I'm so glad I found you.
It feels like-- i-- destiny.

0:27:14.718 --> 0:27:17.508
For what must be the millionth time,
it's not destiny.

0:27:17.679 --> 0:27:19.929
Uh-oh. Have I said "destiny" before?
I'm sorry.

0:27:20.098 --> 0:27:22.178
I'm just so nervous
because I'm gonna meet my parents.

0:27:22.351 --> 0:27:24.561
I haven't seen them in I don't even know
how long because...

0:27:24.728 --> 0:27:26.898
-You see I suffer from short-term--
-short-term memory loss.

0:27:27.064 --> 0:27:28.694
Look, no more talking. Okay?
I don't like talking.

0:27:28.857 --> 0:27:31.227
I don't like chatter and questions.
And, "how are you? Oh I'm fine."

0:27:31.401 --> 0:27:34.571
"How are you? I'm fine too."
News flash -nobody's fine.

0:27:34.738 --> 0:27:35.568
Oh, I'm fine. How are you?

0:27:36.782 --> 0:27:38.912
-Hank, look, there's a map!
-Sh!

0:27:38.951 --> 0:27:41.621
The plan is you're gonna read that
and figure out where your parents live.

0:27:41.745 --> 0:27:43.575
Then I'm on the truck to Cleveland.
You got it?

0:27:43.747 --> 0:27:45.917
Got it. What was the first part again?

0:27:46.083 --> 0:27:47.383
Ugh.

0:27:47.501 --> 0:27:48.591
What? The octopus escaped again?

0:27:48.710 --> 0:27:51.300
Wow. Look at all the exhibits.

0:27:51.421 --> 0:27:53.421
How can you do this park in one day?
Seriously.

0:27:53.590 --> 0:27:54.880
-Pick one!
-Okay.

0:27:55.926 --> 0:27:57.586
Well, tell everyone to keep an eye out.

0:27:57.761 --> 0:28:01.391
We're supposed to be releasing
the octopus back to the ocean today.

0:28:03.934 --> 0:28:06.774
Well, of course I haven't seen him.
If I was looking I'd find him.

0:28:06.937 --> 0:28:08.857
Hank! There you are.

0:28:08.981 --> 0:28:10.481
-Hurry up!
-Okay. Okay.

0:28:10.649 --> 0:28:15.899
K. It starts with a "k."
Kid z-own-y. Kid zone!

0:28:16.071 --> 0:28:17.991
No! No kids. Kids grab things.

0:28:18.073 --> 0:28:19.953
And I'm not losing
another tentacle for you.

0:28:20.117 --> 0:28:22.657
You lost a tentacle?
Well then you're not an octopus,

0:28:22.744 --> 0:28:24.004
you're a septopus.

0:28:24.162 --> 0:28:25.502
I may not remember, but I can count.

0:28:25.664 --> 0:28:26.964
-Hurry up!
-Okay.

0:28:27.082 --> 0:28:30.962
Journey to the-- hey, look. Shells.

0:28:33.130 --> 0:28:37.630
Hey, look. Shells!
Daddy, here's a shell for you.

0:28:37.801 --> 0:28:40.301
That's great, dory.
You found another one.

0:28:40.470 --> 0:28:42.510
-I did?
-Oh, yes, you did.

0:28:42.681 --> 0:28:44.101
You're getting good at this, dory.

0:28:47.269 --> 0:28:48.649
Hey, look. Shells!

0:28:50.147 --> 0:28:53.227
-Hey, I live there.
-Yes! Yes, indeed.

0:28:53.358 --> 0:28:56.648
-I like shells.
-That's right, dear.

0:28:58.322 --> 0:29:00.492
Do you think you could find me
another shell?

0:29:01.200 --> 0:29:02.830
Purple ones are my favorite.

0:29:04.953 --> 0:29:06.333
Okay, mommy.

0:29:07.998 --> 0:29:12.708
Mommy. Purple shell. Purple shell!
Hey, my home had a purple shell.

0:29:13.212 --> 0:29:15.342
So what? Half the exhibits here
have purple shells in them.

0:29:15.506 --> 0:29:17.336
No, no, no. You don't understand.
I remember her now.

0:29:17.508 --> 0:29:20.388
Purple shells were her favorite
and she had this adorable giggle.

0:29:20.469 --> 0:29:21.549
And then my dad was really friendly.

0:29:21.637 --> 0:29:23.007
And now your wacky memory's
gonna get us caught.

0:29:27.351 --> 0:29:28.641
Still think this is destiny?

0:29:28.810 --> 0:29:30.310
-Hank, we have to find my folks!
-Quiet!

0:29:37.027 --> 0:29:40.407
Ugh. Base, this is Carol.

0:29:40.572 --> 0:29:43.702
I think I might have found
that missing octopus. Over.

0:29:44.743 --> 0:29:46.083
-See what you did?
-Sorry.

0:29:46.245 --> 0:29:47.205
This could not be worse.

0:29:47.246 --> 0:29:51.416
Hmm. "Destiny." Destiny.

0:29:52.084 --> 0:29:55.884
Hank. I got a feeling.
I think we should get in the bucket.

0:29:56.046 --> 0:29:58.206
-No. Stop.
-Seriously. It says "destiny" and it is--

0:29:58.382 --> 0:29:59.922
-no, no, no, no, no.
-We've got to get in that bucket.

0:30:00.050 --> 0:30:04.350
-I'm not going with you in that bucket.
-Here...I...Go...In...The...Bucket. Bye.

0:30:06.765 --> 0:30:11.555
Hey, guys, I'm looking for my family.
Oh, good idea. Play dead.

0:30:18.277 --> 0:30:21.647
I'm sorry. I got to blink. How do you
hold your eyes open that long?

0:30:32.916 --> 0:30:35.956
Hey, guys. Wait a second.

0:30:43.010 --> 0:30:45.760
Our next guest
has been here a very long time.

0:30:45.929 --> 0:30:49.929
She's a whale shark.
Her name is destiny.

0:30:50.058 --> 0:30:51.308
Destiny? Really?

0:30:51.435 --> 0:30:54.485
You'll notice she's extremely
nearsighted and has trouble...

0:30:54.646 --> 0:30:58.896
Navigating her environment.
Oh! And here she comes now.

0:30:59.026 --> 0:31:02.486
Ooh! Destiny. You're a fish?

0:31:04.406 --> 0:31:05.866
Wait. What?

0:31:05.991 --> 0:31:08.991
-Hi! Hello there.
-Whoa! Oh. Whoa.

0:31:10.454 --> 0:31:12.124
All right, I'll go with you.

0:31:12.998 --> 0:31:16.458
-Excuse me.
-Is that blue blob talking?

0:31:16.585 --> 0:31:18.965
-Can you help me? I lost my family.
-You lost your family?

0:31:19.129 --> 0:31:20.379
Well, it's a long story,

0:31:20.464 --> 0:31:22.174
and truth be told,
i don't remember most of it.

0:31:22.299 --> 0:31:23.879
Aw, that is so sad. You poor thi--

0:31:27.304 --> 0:31:30.644
sorry. Not a great swimmer.
I can't see very well.

0:31:30.807 --> 0:31:32.267
Oh, I think you swim beautifully.

0:31:32.309 --> 0:31:34.309
In fact, I've never seen a fish
swim like that before.

0:31:34.478 --> 0:31:36.188
Thank you.

0:31:36.313 --> 0:31:38.823
You're welcome.

0:31:38.982 --> 0:31:40.112
Wait. Say that again.

0:31:40.234 --> 0:31:43.154
You're welcome.

0:31:43.320 --> 0:31:44.820
-Dory?
-Yes.

0:31:44.988 --> 0:31:45.988
-Dory?
-Yes.

0:31:46.114 --> 0:31:47.074
-Dory?
-Yes.

0:31:47.199 --> 0:31:48.779
-Dory!
-Yes.

0:31:48.909 --> 0:31:51.079
-You and I were friends!
-No!

0:31:51.203 --> 0:31:53.163
-Dory, it's me! Destiny!
-You know me?

0:31:53.330 --> 0:31:56.000
Of course! We talked through the pipes
when we were little.

0:31:56.166 --> 0:31:57.786
-We were pipe pals!
-We were?

0:31:58.377 --> 0:32:01.207
-Aw, you're so pretty.
-So you know where I'm from?

0:32:01.380 --> 0:32:03.260
Yep, you are from
the open ocean exhibit.

0:32:03.757 --> 0:32:05.177
I'm from the open ocean exhibit?

0:32:05.342 --> 0:32:08.262
Then that's where my parents are.
We got to go. Can you take me there?

0:32:08.428 --> 0:32:11.098
Kind of tough for a whale
to travel around here.

0:32:11.265 --> 0:32:14.565
Can you please keep it down
over there? My head hurts.

0:32:14.726 --> 0:32:16.686
-Who's that?
-That's my neighbor, Bailey.

0:32:16.854 --> 0:32:18.194
He was brought in with a head injury.

0:32:18.355 --> 0:32:19.435
I know you're talking about me, destiny.

0:32:19.606 --> 0:32:21.726
He thinks he can't use his echolocation,
but I've overheard...

0:32:21.900 --> 0:32:23.940
The doctors talking.
There's not a thing wrong with him.

0:32:24.111 --> 0:32:26.031
Hear every word
you're saying about me.

0:32:26.154 --> 0:32:27.204
What's echolocation?

0:32:27.364 --> 0:32:30.284
Bailey's head is supposed to put out
a call and the echo helps him...

0:32:30.450 --> 0:32:35.500
Find objects far away.
Oh, but apparently he's still "healing."

0:32:35.622 --> 0:32:39.382
Now I know you're talking about me.
I really can't echolocate.

0:32:39.543 --> 0:32:41.253
I cannot have this conversation again.
I just can't.

0:32:41.420 --> 0:32:44.460
I hit my head very hard out there.
See how swollen it is!

0:32:44.631 --> 0:32:46.931
Your head is supposed to be big!
You're a beluga!

0:32:47.092 --> 0:32:51.512
Echolocation. Oh, like the world's
most powerful pair of glasses?

0:32:51.555 --> 0:32:52.725
-What?
-What are glasses?

0:32:52.848 --> 0:32:57.518
It's sort of like you go, "hoo" and then
you see things. Why do I know that?

0:32:57.644 --> 0:33:00.064
Oh. That's interesting.

0:33:02.733 --> 0:33:05.443
There you are!
Listen up, you and I are square.

0:33:05.611 --> 0:33:08.111
I took you to the map,
now give me that tag!

0:33:08.280 --> 0:33:10.320
Wait, no. I know where my parents are.
They're in the--

0:33:10.490 --> 0:33:13.330
what's it called? The place--
the soap and lotion?

0:33:13.493 --> 0:33:15.163
-Open ocean.
-Open ocean!

0:33:15.329 --> 0:33:17.789
Open ocean! I know where that is.

0:33:17.956 --> 0:33:21.076
That's the exhibit located right next to--
i don't care.

0:33:21.251 --> 0:33:22.091
Easy!

0:33:22.169 --> 0:33:25.089
If you're trying to get to the open ocean
exhibit go through the pipes.

0:33:25.255 --> 0:33:27.465
-Through the pipes. Great.
-Through the pipes?

0:33:27.633 --> 0:33:29.633
Yep. Take two lefts, swim straight
and you'll hit it.

0:33:29.801 --> 0:33:33.891
Oh, that's a lot of directions. That's--
did you get that, Hank? All that?

0:33:34.014 --> 0:33:35.934
-Yeah.
-Great! Let's go.

0:33:36.433 --> 0:33:39.523
I'm not going with you. I won't fit.
You have to go by yourself.

0:33:43.273 --> 0:33:48.323
That's-- I'm-- i-- see, I can't because
I'm not so good with directions.

0:33:48.487 --> 0:33:51.527
Well, that's too bad. A deal's a deal.
You wanted to find your parents?

0:33:51.698 --> 0:33:53.658
That's how you get to them.
Now give me your tag.

0:33:53.825 --> 0:33:56.655
But, Hank, I can't go in the pipes alone.
I'll forget where I'm going.

0:33:56.787 --> 0:33:59.707
-Not my problem. Tag!
-But I can't get in that way.

0:33:59.831 --> 0:34:02.131
-I'm sorry, but there's no other way.
-There's no other way.

0:34:04.795 --> 0:34:08.135
-There's no other way.
-Now, now. Don't panic.

0:34:08.298 --> 0:34:12.338
It's okay. Not everything in life is
easy to do. Isn't that right, Charlie?

0:34:12.511 --> 0:34:16.641
She's right. When something's
too hard, you should just give up.

0:34:16.807 --> 0:34:18.727
-Charlie!
-A joke. I'm kidding!

0:34:18.892 --> 0:34:22.522
Just a joke. A joke.
Caution, joker at work.

0:34:22.688 --> 0:34:23.978
Joke. I got it.

0:34:24.147 --> 0:34:27.317
You see, kelpcake?
There's always another way.

0:34:29.361 --> 0:34:30.861
Thank you, daddy.

0:34:32.155 --> 0:34:36.325
Thank you, daddy. Nope. My father
said there's always another way.

0:34:36.410 --> 0:34:39.500
-What? There is no other way.
-Open ocean. Open ocean.

0:34:40.080 --> 0:34:43.250
Open ocean. I'm pretty sure
it's the building over there.

0:34:43.333 --> 0:34:46.593
That's ill-defined and roundish.
Like Bailey's head.

0:34:46.753 --> 0:34:48.713
-Wait, what?
-Always another way. There's--

0:34:48.881 --> 0:34:52.841
there! Guys, follow me. I know
how we can get to locomotion.

0:34:53.010 --> 0:34:54.340
-Open ocean.
-Exactly.

0:34:55.095 --> 0:34:57.095
Guys. You know I can't swim
over there, right?

0:34:59.600 --> 0:35:02.520
Ooo-roo, ooo-roo, ooo-roo.

0:35:02.603 --> 0:35:06.113
I don't see how this is going to get us
inside. What are you even doing?

0:35:06.273 --> 0:35:08.023
We're calling her over, of course.

0:35:08.192 --> 0:35:09.942
Calling her over? Calling who over?

0:35:14.823 --> 0:35:16.993
Lads, meet Becky.

0:35:18.869 --> 0:35:22.619
Flying? No, no, no new information.

0:35:22.789 --> 0:35:26.539
Listen, tell her thank you. You guys
have gone above and beyond. Really.

0:35:26.710 --> 0:35:30.920
But is there a way to get in
that involves, like, swimming?

0:35:31.089 --> 0:35:32.469
Because that's really our strength.

0:35:32.549 --> 0:35:35.179
Look, your friend is going to be
in quarantine.

0:35:35.302 --> 0:35:37.392
That's where they take the sick fish.

0:35:37.471 --> 0:35:41.021
And the one and only one way
into that place is Becky.

0:35:44.102 --> 0:35:48.442
Hi, Becky. Ow! Stop. Let's call
her pecky because this is hurting.

0:35:48.607 --> 0:35:49.937
I think she likes you, dad.

0:35:50.108 --> 0:35:55.068
Becky, love? These two nice fish
need to get into quarantine.

0:35:55.239 --> 0:35:57.069
Are you free today, Rebecca darling?

0:35:57.199 --> 0:36:00.949
Becky, is-- would that work
with your schedule? Ow!

0:36:01.119 --> 0:36:02.869
She doesn't understand
what I'm saying.

0:36:02.996 --> 0:36:05.576
All you have to do
is imprint with her, mate.

0:36:05.707 --> 0:36:07.327
-Imp-- what?
-Imprint.

0:36:07.501 --> 0:36:11.591
Look her in the eye and say, "ooo-roo"
and she'll be in sync with you.

0:36:11.755 --> 0:36:14.835
-Now look her in the eye.
-Yeah.

0:36:15.467 --> 0:36:18.927
Nemo, I think we should devise
an alternate plan.

0:36:19.096 --> 0:36:21.766
One that involves staying in the water
and someone sane.

0:36:21.932 --> 0:36:24.982
Because this bird, this bird...
This ain't the bird!

0:36:25.143 --> 0:36:27.943
That's fine, dad. And in the meantime,
dory will just forget us.

0:36:28.105 --> 0:36:29.985
Like you said, it's what she does best.

0:36:30.148 --> 0:36:31.778
Fine.

0:36:34.278 --> 0:36:38.738
Okay, look her in the eye. Which eye?

0:36:38.866 --> 0:36:40.116
Just pick one, mate.

0:36:40.284 --> 0:36:41.124
Becky.

0:36:46.456 --> 0:36:51.126
Ooh. Ooo-roo. Roo-roo, Becky.

0:36:53.839 --> 0:36:56.339
Okay, this is all great.

0:36:57.801 --> 0:37:00.721
How exactly is Becky
supposed to carry us?

0:37:00.846 --> 0:37:04.636
Oh yeah. I almost forgot. Gerald!

0:37:04.808 --> 0:37:06.388
-Hmm?
-Yeah, Gerald.

0:37:06.560 --> 0:37:08.190
-Come on, son.
-Hmm?

0:37:08.687 --> 0:37:12.977
Come on, Gerald. Give us your pail,
we'll let you sit on the rock.

0:37:13.150 --> 0:37:15.820
-Yeah, Gerald. We swear it.
-Hmm.

0:37:17.654 --> 0:37:20.414
That's right. Shimmy on over here.

0:37:20.574 --> 0:37:22.584
Come on. You can do it.

0:37:23.327 --> 0:37:24.407
That's right.

0:37:24.578 --> 0:37:26.038
Mind you don't scuff your bum.

0:37:28.832 --> 0:37:31.582
Thank you so much, Gerald.

0:37:31.752 --> 0:37:34.382
Welcome to your time on this rock.

0:37:35.923 --> 0:37:37.053
Comfortable, isn't it?

0:37:38.675 --> 0:37:41.755
-Time's up! Get off! Off! Off! Off! Off!
-Time's up! Now get off, Gerald! Off!

0:37:41.887 --> 0:37:46.177
No, this is nuts! Why do I keep getting
talked into insane choices?

0:37:46.225 --> 0:37:47.275
Good luck!

0:37:52.439 --> 0:37:54.069
Okay, when I tell you you're gonna--

0:37:54.233 --> 0:37:56.113
yeah. I know. I'm gonna signal
with a big splash.

0:37:56.276 --> 0:38:00.856
On my mark. Not clear yet.
Not clear yet.

0:38:01.323 --> 0:38:03.583
-Now?
-Not 'til destiny gives the signal.

0:38:05.118 --> 0:38:08.248
You know something? I have no idea
why you're even doing this.

0:38:09.373 --> 0:38:10.213
What do you mean?

0:38:10.374 --> 0:38:12.214
It seems like a lot of trouble
just to find some more fish.

0:38:12.376 --> 0:38:14.206
If I had short-term memory loss...

0:38:14.378 --> 0:38:16.208
I'd just swim off into the blue
and forget everything.

0:38:16.380 --> 0:38:18.050
Well I don't want to do that.
I want my family.

0:38:18.215 --> 0:38:20.265
Not me, kid. I don't want anyone
to worry about.

0:38:20.801 --> 0:38:24.721
You're lucky. No memories.
No problems.

0:38:24.888 --> 0:38:28.018
Huh. No memories. No problems.

0:38:28.058 --> 0:38:31.308
Still not clear. Still not clear.

0:38:31.478 --> 0:38:32.808
You don't have to say when it's not time.

0:38:32.980 --> 0:38:34.310
-Not--
-just tell me when it is time.

0:38:34.481 --> 0:38:36.231
Okay, here we go. And-- wait!

0:38:36.400 --> 0:38:38.070
"Here we go. Wait." Are you serious?

0:38:38.235 --> 0:38:39.865
-Okay, on the count of three.
-Don't count. Just say, "go."

0:38:39.987 --> 0:38:41.737
-Go! Now, now. Do it! Do it!
-What? Okay, okay.

0:38:42.322 --> 0:38:44.622
-Wow. Look at that! I mean--
-that's the signal.

0:38:44.741 --> 0:38:45.871
Go, go, go! That's the signal!

0:38:51.582 --> 0:38:56.092
Now remember, destiny said follow
the signs to the open ocean exhibit.

0:38:56.253 --> 0:38:59.763
I can't see squat,
so it's your job to look for it.

0:38:59.923 --> 0:39:01.263
Got it. Follow the signs to open ocean.

0:39:01.300 --> 0:39:03.590
I'm just gonna repeat it, okay?
That should work.

0:39:03.635 --> 0:39:06.505
Follow the signs to open ocean.
Follow the signs to open ocean.

0:39:06.597 --> 0:39:09.427
Mm. Go right! Follow the signs
to open ocean.

0:39:09.516 --> 0:39:12.936
Follow the signs to open ocean.
Follow the signs to open ocean. Left!

0:39:13.103 --> 0:39:15.023
-Follow the signs to open ocean.
-And steer clear of people, will you?

0:39:15.189 --> 0:39:17.399
Especially kids.
I don't want to be touched.

0:39:17.441 --> 0:39:18.981
Sh! Do not mess me up!

0:39:21.612 --> 0:39:25.032
Oh, poor baby. Let me get that for you.
Here you-- oh!

0:39:26.533 --> 0:39:27.623
Oh my.

0:39:28.702 --> 0:39:30.622
Where do we go? Where do we go?

0:39:30.787 --> 0:39:33.667
Oh, sorry!
Okay, I was looking, looking...

0:39:33.832 --> 0:39:36.582
Roo-roo, Becky! Drop us anywhere.
We're okay.

0:39:36.710 --> 0:39:39.840
Just wait, dad. I think she's looking
for a place to land.

0:39:40.005 --> 0:39:43.675
She's confused, Nemo. She doesn't
even know which way to look.

0:39:50.140 --> 0:39:54.310
Wait, Becky. What are you doing?
Ooo-roo. Ooo-roo-roo-roo-roo.

0:39:55.729 --> 0:39:59.149
Okay. I was going somewhere.
The question is where.

0:39:59.316 --> 0:40:01.646
Which way? Do you see the sign?

0:40:01.693 --> 0:40:04.653
I'm looking. I'm looking. Something to
something gets me to my family!

0:40:04.738 --> 0:40:07.278
"The world's most powerful pair of--"

0:40:07.407 --> 0:40:10.407
I know that. Why do I know that?
It's another memory.

0:40:10.577 --> 0:40:13.197
Hank, we need to go that way!
Left. Go left.

0:40:17.334 --> 0:40:20.004
Becky! Ooo-roo. Ooo-roo.

0:40:20.087 --> 0:40:22.047
She can't hear you, dad.

0:40:22.130 --> 0:40:26.010
All right. New plan. We have to
get closer to Becky so she can hear us.

0:40:27.010 --> 0:40:28.850
I don't think we should move the pail.

0:40:29.471 --> 0:40:33.021
Nemo. Without me Becky's lost.

0:40:33.517 --> 0:40:35.187
Dad, just trust her.

0:40:35.269 --> 0:40:38.229
Trust her? So she can forget us
all together?

0:40:38.397 --> 0:40:42.027
-I trust Becky.
-You trust her? Becky's eating a cup!

0:40:44.027 --> 0:40:47.357
Becky! Becky! Ooo-roo! Whoa!

0:40:55.122 --> 0:40:58.462
Well, at least we're not stuck
in the bucket anymore.

0:41:03.505 --> 0:41:05.125
Or on top of quarantine.

0:41:06.008 --> 0:41:07.468
The baby otter talk is beginning now.

0:41:07.634 --> 0:41:12.064
Why, thanks, sigourney Weaver.
Hey, who wants to learn about otters?

0:41:12.222 --> 0:41:15.562
Looking for the world's
most powerful pair of glasses.

0:41:15.893 --> 0:41:17.063
Otters!

0:41:17.227 --> 0:41:19.307
-Welcome, it's a huge cuddle party!
-Cuddle party! I'm in!

0:41:21.565 --> 0:41:24.235
Where are we?
Are we close to open ocean?

0:41:24.401 --> 0:41:26.781
Yes. I think-- well, I don't know.
But I saw that other sign so--

0:41:26.945 --> 0:41:27.895
what? What other sign?

0:41:28.071 --> 0:41:29.411
The world's most powerful pair
of glasses.

0:41:29.573 --> 0:41:32.283
What? What are you talking about?
Why would we follow that sign?

0:41:32.409 --> 0:41:34.619
Well, because I remembered it.

0:41:34.745 --> 0:41:36.505
No. That wasn't the plan. Ow!

0:41:38.582 --> 0:41:41.502
All right, that's it!
You have wasted my time!

0:41:41.585 --> 0:41:43.675
-Wait. No.
-That transport truck leaves at dawn...

0:41:43.837 --> 0:41:45.627
And I'm not missing it,
so give me your tag.

0:41:45.797 --> 0:41:47.257
Wait. No, I remembered that sign.

0:41:47.424 --> 0:41:49.054
-So?
-So I'm remembering more...

0:41:49.092 --> 0:41:51.432
And more and I feel like my memory's
getting better. I think we should--

0:41:51.595 --> 0:41:54.265
no! Your memory is not working.
You can't remember anything.

0:41:54.431 --> 0:41:57.101
It's probably how you lost your family
in the first place!

0:41:59.978 --> 0:42:03.858
All right, look, let's just take it down
a notch. Just give me the tag and--

0:42:04.024 --> 0:42:07.284
you know something, for a guy with
three hearts you're not very nice.

0:42:07.444 --> 0:42:09.654
Three hearts? What are you
talking about? I don't have three hearts.

0:42:09.738 --> 0:42:10.948
-Yes, you do.
-I don't!

0:42:10.989 --> 0:42:11.779
-You do!
-Don't!

0:42:11.949 --> 0:42:13.069
-Do!
-Stop saying that!

0:42:13.200 --> 0:42:16.330
Fun fact- the octopus has three hearts.

0:42:16.411 --> 0:42:18.621
Two pump blood to the gills
while the third pumps...

