I say we go this way. Follow me.
It's time to head home!

0:58:25.756 --> 0:58:29.176
Wait, wait, wait! My parents are here.

0:58:29.301 --> 0:58:31.091
-They are?
-You found your parents?

0:58:31.261 --> 0:58:35.601
Well, not exactly. No. I mean not yet,
but I know where they are.

0:58:35.766 --> 0:58:40.056
I don't know exactly how to get there,
but I know that-- I'm getting help--

0:58:40.229 --> 0:58:41.939
-down to quarantine.
-Quarantine.

0:58:42.105 --> 0:58:45.775
That's it! Oh, and I met
this septopus, super cranky...

0:58:45.943 --> 0:58:50.953
But secretly kind of sweet, and he
got me into the exhibit... the exhibit.

0:58:53.450 --> 0:58:54.450
Dory?

0:58:55.285 --> 0:58:57.445
Do you think my parents
will want to see me?

0:58:57.621 --> 0:58:59.961
What?
Why wouldn't they want to see you?

0:59:00.791 --> 0:59:03.961
Because... I lost them?

0:59:04.962 --> 0:59:08.922
Dory, your parents are going to be
overjoyed to see you.

0:59:09.758 --> 0:59:12.798
They're going to have missed...
Everything about you.

0:59:12.970 --> 0:59:15.310
-Really?
-Do you know how we found you?

0:59:15.472 --> 0:59:17.312
-Something about a clam? Or...
-No.

0:59:17.474 --> 0:59:18.314
-No, an oyster.
-No.

0:59:18.475 --> 0:59:19.515
-Mollusk?
-No.

0:59:19.685 --> 0:59:20.355
-Something?
-No.

0:59:20.519 --> 0:59:21.769
-I don't... no?
-No clam.

0:59:21.937 --> 0:59:24.647
We were having a very hard time
until Nemo thought...

0:59:24.815 --> 0:59:26.825
"What would dory do?"

0:59:27.401 --> 0:59:28.651
Why would you say that?

0:59:28.819 --> 0:59:31.819
Because ever since I've met you,
you've shown me how to do...

0:59:31.989 --> 0:59:36.199
Stuff I never dreamed of doing.
Crazy things!

0:59:37.035 --> 0:59:40.535
Outsmarting sharks
and jumping jellyfish.

0:59:41.707 --> 0:59:45.997
And finding my son.
You made all that happen.

0:59:47.212 --> 0:59:52.052
Really? I didn't know you thought that.
Unless I forgot.

0:59:53.302 --> 0:59:56.512
No, you didn't forget. I never told you.

0:59:57.848 --> 0:59:59.518
And I'm sorry about that.

1:00:01.810 --> 1:00:07.650
But, dory, because of who you are,
you are about to find your parents.

1:00:09.651 --> 1:00:15.201
And when you do that, you'll be home.

1:00:27.711 --> 1:00:29.211
Dad.

1:00:29.379 --> 1:00:32.419
Does this mean
we have to say goodbye to dory?

1:00:34.343 --> 1:00:36.393
Yes, Nemo. We do.

1:00:50.400 --> 1:00:54.150
Marine life
institute

1:00:56.448 --> 1:00:58.408
hey, so how much more
we got left to load?

1:00:58.575 --> 1:01:00.075
Just this last row.

1:01:00.244 --> 1:01:02.624
The sooner we finish,
the sooner this truck gets to Cleveland.

1:01:03.080 --> 1:01:05.370
-Watch the turn.
-Watch what? Ow!

1:01:05.541 --> 1:01:08.421
-Too late.
-Okay, I think we're close. Whee!

1:01:10.170 --> 1:01:11.710
Hi!

1:01:11.839 --> 1:01:14.919
-Is this quarantine?
-Yes! This is it! We're in quarantine!

1:01:15.092 --> 1:01:16.432
My parents are here!

1:01:17.594 --> 1:01:20.104
Where are we going? Hey, what--
no, why are we going towards the door?

1:01:20.264 --> 1:01:24.274
-We are all better!
-I feel fantastic!

1:01:25.936 --> 1:01:26.896
Dude.

1:01:29.106 --> 1:01:32.316
My family! Come on, let's go!
Excuse me.

1:01:32.401 --> 1:01:33.571
Dory, wait a minute!

1:01:37.155 --> 1:01:40.775
I'm coming mommy! I'm coming daddy!

1:01:41.743 --> 1:01:44.793
Whoo-hoo! Almost home.
Almost home. I'm almost home.

1:01:44.913 --> 1:01:47.583
I think I'm getting the hang of this! Oh!

1:01:51.420 --> 1:01:52.880
I hear footsteps.

1:01:55.966 --> 1:01:57.006
-Hank!
-Quiet.

1:01:57.259 --> 1:01:59.639
Hank, we need to get in that tank.
That rhymed.

1:01:59.803 --> 1:02:01.643
-Why?
-Her parents are there!

1:02:03.182 --> 1:02:07.142
Look, you've got three minutes
to get everyone in this cup with you...

1:02:07.311 --> 1:02:09.151
And then I'm on that truck
to Cleveland, got it?

1:02:09.313 --> 1:02:10.193
Got it.

1:02:14.693 --> 1:02:15.943
Oh boy.

1:02:20.407 --> 1:02:22.117
Mom? Dad?

1:02:22.284 --> 1:02:26.624
Mom? Dad?
Hey, everybody. It's me, dory!

1:02:26.788 --> 1:02:30.328
Dory? Dory? Dory?
Jenny and Charlie's dory? Dory?

1:02:30.459 --> 1:02:32.169
Mom? Dad?

1:02:33.003 --> 1:02:34.503
Mom? Dad?

1:02:35.839 --> 1:02:37.799
Mom? Dad?

1:02:38.717 --> 1:02:41.337
-She should just pick 2 and let's go.
-Dad.

1:02:41.512 --> 1:02:43.932
What? I'm kidding. It's a reunion.

1:02:44.056 --> 1:02:47.846
Mom? Dad? Where are my parents?

1:02:48.852 --> 1:02:51.942
Dory? Are you really
Jenny and Charlie's girl?

1:02:52.064 --> 1:02:55.034
Yes, I am! That's me! Where are they?

1:02:55.150 --> 1:02:58.360
Dory, right after you disappeared,
they thought you...

1:02:58.529 --> 1:03:01.869
Well, they thought you must have
ended up here, in quarantine.

1:03:01.949 --> 1:03:04.869
-Uh-huh?
-Come on, come on, come on.

1:03:04.993 --> 1:03:08.543
And so they came here to look for you.

1:03:08.705 --> 1:03:10.365
They're here! Where are they?

1:03:12.668 --> 1:03:16.208
Dory, that was years ago.

1:03:16.380 --> 1:03:19.220
-Huh?
-They never came back.

1:03:19.341 --> 1:03:20.471
Oh no.

1:03:20.592 --> 1:03:24.972
You see, dory, when fish
don't come back from quarantine...

1:03:25.097 --> 1:03:27.307
It means they're not...

1:03:28.016 --> 1:03:28.926
What?

1:03:29.560 --> 1:03:31.770
Dory, they're gone.

1:03:32.521 --> 1:03:34.231
They're dead?

1:03:34.982 --> 1:03:38.572
-They wanted to find you...
-Wait. Are you sure they're gone?

1:03:39.403 --> 1:03:41.533
Dory, listen, it's going to be okay.

1:03:41.697 --> 1:03:43.067
Dory, they loved you so much.

1:03:43.240 --> 1:03:46.080
Anyone not looking to go to Cleveland,
final warning!

1:03:48.787 --> 1:03:51.617
-Dory, are you all right?
-Are you okay?

1:03:51.748 --> 1:03:54.918
-I was too late.
-Dory, no. No. Now listen.

1:03:55.085 --> 1:03:58.915
-I don't have a family.
-No, dory. That's not true.

1:03:59.590 --> 1:04:01.800
Time to go!

1:04:01.967 --> 1:04:03.797
I'm all alone.

1:04:03.969 --> 1:04:05.469
-Dory.
-Dory!

1:04:07.723 --> 1:04:09.143
Where's everybody else?

1:04:10.100 --> 1:04:12.600
Your orange friends are on their way
to Cleveland. Ah!

1:04:12.769 --> 1:04:14.099
I found the octopus!

1:04:15.731 --> 1:04:16.941
Where did he go?

1:04:25.782 --> 1:04:27.912
Mommy? Daddy?

1:04:34.458 --> 1:04:35.458
Help.

1:04:37.294 --> 1:04:41.804
No. No. No. Help. Help. Help me.

1:04:41.965 --> 1:04:47.295
Help. Help me. Please.
Somebody help me!

1:04:48.639 --> 1:04:51.019
Hey, can-- help me?
Can you help me? I've lost them!

1:04:51.183 --> 1:04:54.523
-Oh. Lost who?
-I-i-i-i...

1:04:54.686 --> 1:04:57.516
Ah, sorry, honey. I can't help you
if you don't remember.

1:05:00.943 --> 1:05:04.033
Oh! Can you help me? I've lost...Them.

1:05:04.196 --> 1:05:05.526
Can you be more specific?

1:05:05.697 --> 1:05:07.947
My-- my-- them! Them! Them!

1:05:14.498 --> 1:05:16.828
Help! Help!

1:05:18.335 --> 1:05:20.955
Please? They're gone!

1:05:35.310 --> 1:05:40.150
I've lost... I've lost everyone.
There's nothing I can do.

1:05:42.234 --> 1:05:46.534
Shoot, I can't forget.
What was I forgetting? Something.

1:05:47.865 --> 1:05:50.415
Something important. What was it? I--

1:05:52.202 --> 1:05:55.542
what was it? It's going away.

1:05:56.373 --> 1:06:00.383
It's going away. It's going because
all I can do is forget. I just forget.

1:06:00.544 --> 1:06:04.674
And I forget. That's what I do best.
That's what I do.

1:06:06.008 --> 1:06:10.548
What do I do? What do I do?
What do I do? What do I do?

1:06:12.556 --> 1:06:14.216
What would dory do?

1:06:16.894 --> 1:06:18.734
I would look around.

1:06:21.231 --> 1:06:25.071
And there's just water over there.
And a lot of kelp over here.

1:06:26.069 --> 1:06:27.739
Kelp is better. Okay.

1:06:33.452 --> 1:06:38.042
Okay. Now what? Lots of kelp.
It looks the same.

1:06:39.374 --> 1:06:43.754
It all looks the same,
except there's a rock...Over there.

1:06:44.421 --> 1:06:49.381
And some sand this way.
I like sand. Sand is squishy.

1:07:05.108 --> 1:07:06.608
Oh this isn't going anywhere.

1:07:08.737 --> 1:07:13.827
There's nothing here.
Nothing but kelp. Lots of kelp.

1:07:13.992 --> 1:07:18.122
And some shells...This way.

1:07:19.456 --> 1:07:20.786
I like shells.

1:07:24.336 --> 1:07:27.756
I like...Shells.

1:07:54.116 --> 1:07:55.446
Whoa.

1:08:32.905 --> 1:08:34.495
Hello. I'm--

1:08:34.615 --> 1:08:37.915
-dory!
-Dory! You're here.

1:08:38.076 --> 1:08:39.826
-Oh my baby!
-You're really here.

1:08:39.995 --> 1:08:41.045
-Let me look at you.
-You found us.

1:08:41.205 --> 1:08:43.375
-I'm never letting you go again.
-Oh my missing girl, you're here.

1:08:43.498 --> 1:08:44.538
-My baby!
-It's you.

1:08:44.708 --> 1:08:48.378
-Yes! Oh absolutely!
-It's really you! Mom, you're here.

1:08:48.545 --> 1:08:51.205
-I am, I...
-And dad, so are you.

1:08:51.298 --> 1:08:52.838
Right here, kelpcake.

1:08:56.386 --> 1:08:58.046
I'm so sorry.

1:08:58.222 --> 1:09:00.892
Oh honey. Oh honey, no. Kelpcake.

1:09:01.058 --> 1:09:04.728
I know I've got a problem. I know I'm--
and I'm so sorry.

1:09:04.895 --> 1:09:09.025
And all this time I've wanted to fix it
and I can't and I try. I try.

1:09:09.066 --> 1:09:11.896
But my thoughts --they leave my head
and ideas change.

1:09:12.069 --> 1:09:14.199
And I'd forgotten you and I'm so sorry.

1:09:14.363 --> 1:09:19.413
Dory. Don't you dare be sorry.
Look what you did.

1:09:20.077 --> 1:09:23.247
-What?
-You found us!

1:09:23.413 --> 1:09:25.173
That's right. You found us.

1:09:26.667 --> 1:09:30.127
Honey, why do you think
we stayed put here all these years?

1:09:30.295 --> 1:09:34.125
Because we believed one day
you'd find us again.

1:09:34.258 --> 1:09:35.428
Exactly!

1:09:36.134 --> 1:09:39.104
But I thought you were gone.
How did you--

1:09:39.179 --> 1:09:42.219
we went into quarantine to look for you,
but you weren't there.

1:09:42.391 --> 1:09:45.391
And we knew you must have
gotten out through the pipes.

1:09:45.561 --> 1:09:47.771
Through the pipes.
That's right, sweetie. And so we did too.

1:09:47.938 --> 1:09:51.778
And we've stayed in this spot for you
ever since.

1:09:51.942 --> 1:09:54.282
-We thought you might come back.
-We stayed and waited for you.

1:09:54.444 --> 1:09:57.454
So every day, we go out and lay out...

1:09:58.407 --> 1:09:59.487
Shells.

1:10:04.955 --> 1:10:09.795
And you found us.
Oh honey, you found us.

1:10:09.960 --> 1:10:12.460
And you know why you found us?
Because you remembered.

1:10:14.006 --> 1:10:18.926
You remembered
in your own, amazing, dory way.

1:10:21.430 --> 1:10:24.310
I did. All by myself.

1:10:24.474 --> 1:10:29.984
Oh, honey. Really? Have you been
by yourself all these years?

1:10:30.147 --> 1:10:31.817
Oh, my poor little girl.

1:10:31.982 --> 1:10:35.822
Oh, I haven't been all by myself--
marlin and Nemo!

1:10:36.778 --> 1:10:38.948
-Nobody saw where dory went?
-No. Sorry. I didn't see anything.

1:10:39.114 --> 1:10:42.034
Seriously?
That's a lot of eyeballs doing nothing.

1:10:42.284 --> 1:10:43.874
Oh! Oh, excuse me. Can you help us?

1:10:44.036 --> 1:10:45.536
-We're looking--
-me help you?

1:10:49.333 --> 1:10:51.173
Dad, look! It's dory.

1:10:51.293 --> 1:10:55.763
Oh, thank goodness. See, Nemo,
i knew she'd find a way-- what?

1:10:55.881 --> 1:10:57.341
Hey, where's dory? Is she with you?

1:10:58.175 --> 1:11:02.515
I'm sorry. I tried to hold on,
but I couldn't and I lost her.

1:11:02.638 --> 1:11:04.598
-What?
-All right. Let's get going.

1:11:04.723 --> 1:11:05.893
No!

1:11:06.016 --> 1:11:08.556
And then the whale swallowed us
even though I speak whale.

1:11:08.727 --> 1:11:10.347
-A whale?
-Good thing I wasn't there to see that.

1:11:10.521 --> 1:11:12.811
Actually marlin never believes
i even know how to speak whale...

1:11:12.981 --> 1:11:14.861
But you know what, he always kind of
trusts me anyway.

1:11:15.025 --> 1:11:16.525
You know, I like this marlin already.

1:11:16.693 --> 1:11:19.153
Yeah. And then somehow
we found Nemo. Or did he find me?

1:11:19.321 --> 1:11:21.741
I don't know. But, you know what,
Nemo is the sweetest.

1:11:21.907 --> 1:11:23.617
He just never gives up on me
no matter what.

1:11:23.700 --> 1:11:24.870
What would dory do?

1:11:25.035 --> 1:11:27.825
Well, we'll certainly have to thank
marlin and Nemo when we meet them.

1:11:29.373 --> 1:11:31.543
Wait. Wait I know this place.

1:11:31.750 --> 1:11:34.750
Hello. I'm sigourney Weaver.

1:11:34.878 --> 1:11:37.548
-There!
-Won't you please join us?

1:11:37.589 --> 1:11:40.719
-That's the marine life institute.
-Oh, you were born there.

1:11:40.884 --> 1:11:41.724
Dory, is that where your friends are?

1:11:41.885 --> 1:11:45.925
Yes! They were stuck in something.
It was going somewhere.

1:11:46.890 --> 1:11:48.980
A truck. They're in the truck!

1:11:49.059 --> 1:11:51.059
That means I could--
never see them again!

1:11:51.228 --> 1:11:53.268
No! No, no, no. What would dory do?

1:11:54.231 --> 1:11:58.401
I know they're good friends of yours,
but a truck is kind of a tall order.

1:11:59.486 --> 1:12:01.736
Please! Please.
All I know is that I miss them. I-- I...

1:12:01.905 --> 1:12:06.735
I really miss them. I've said that before.

1:12:09.371 --> 1:12:10.411
Dory?

1:12:10.539 --> 1:12:15.249
Mom, marlin and Nemo are more
than good friends, they're family.

1:12:15.419 --> 1:12:19.299
And I have to get them back.
See, when they found me it felt like fate.

1:12:19.423 --> 1:12:22.093
Do you know what I mean? Or... I don't--
what's another word for fate?

1:12:22.259 --> 1:12:27.259
Like destiny. Destiny? Destiny!

1:12:27.639 --> 1:12:29.559
-Dory?
-Destiny!

1:12:29.725 --> 1:12:32.985
-Morning, dest--
-sh. It's dory. Something's wrong.

1:12:34.771 --> 1:12:38.111
Ooh. I got her.
She's right outside the institute.

1:12:39.902 --> 1:12:41.072
-Destiny?
-We got to jump.

1:12:41.236 --> 1:12:42.816
-Jump?
-No time to argue!

1:12:42.946 --> 1:12:44.446
Destiny!

1:12:44.573 --> 1:12:47.453
Dory! The truck thing
with your friends is leaving!

1:12:47.618 --> 1:12:51.748
-No, no. Destiny.
-Oh no! That's bad! What do we do?

1:12:54.208 --> 1:12:56.078
-All right.
-Yes.

1:12:56.126 --> 1:12:57.996
-Here we go. One. Two.
-Yes. Yes.

1:12:58.086 --> 1:12:59.956
I can't! I can't do it!
I'll never make it out there.

1:13:00.214 --> 1:13:03.634
Destiny! I've got the world's
most powerful pair of glasses.

1:13:03.800 --> 1:13:05.470
You've got the world's
most powerful pair of glasses.

1:13:05.636 --> 1:13:06.966
I will be your eyes.

1:13:07.137 --> 1:13:09.467
You can be my eyes. But the walls!

1:13:09.598 --> 1:13:11.678
There are no walls in the ocean!

1:13:12.309 --> 1:13:15.439
-No walls?
-It's your destiny, destiny.

1:13:15.562 --> 1:13:17.612
Well, why didn't you say so?

1:13:17.773 --> 1:13:21.153
What? No! Destiny, wait!
No, that's a wall! Wall!

1:13:26.490 --> 1:13:29.200
Mom, dad, this is my pipe pal.
Destiny, say hi.

1:13:29.368 --> 1:13:31.288
Dory! Are these little blue blobs
your parents?

1:13:31.328 --> 1:13:32.698
They look just like you!

1:13:33.372 --> 1:13:36.002
Hello. I'm Bailey. Mrs. dory, Mr. dory.

1:13:36.166 --> 1:13:37.536
-Oh please, call me Jenny.
-Oh and I'm Charlie.

1:13:37.709 --> 1:13:39.539
Okay. Okay. We got to go.
We got to stop that truck.

1:13:40.170 --> 1:13:41.050
Okay, what truck?

1:13:43.841 --> 1:13:45.181
Bailey, status report.

1:13:45.342 --> 1:13:48.512
Oh, yes, my beautiful gift. Ooh.

1:13:48.679 --> 1:13:50.849
Found it! The truck's merging
onto the freeway

1:13:50.931 --> 1:13:52.351
and it's heading south. Ooh.

1:13:52.516 --> 1:13:54.806
Let's go. We are stopping that truck.

1:13:56.228 --> 1:13:58.978
-This I've got to see.
-Yeah, yeah, me too!

1:13:59.690 --> 1:14:01.320
Oh boy, this is gonna be good!

1:14:02.192 --> 1:14:04.282
What the-- Gerald!
Have you lost your marbles?

1:14:04.820 --> 1:14:07.320
-Don't get used to it, Gerald!
-Cheeky joke.

1:14:10.534 --> 1:14:12.414
Bailey, I forgot everything.
Catch me up.

1:14:12.578 --> 1:14:15.538
Yes, ma'am. Ooh.
Your friends are still on the truck.

1:14:15.706 --> 1:14:18.246
Ooh. They're headed north
towards the bridge. Ooh.

1:14:18.417 --> 1:14:22.337
Oh, look, there's a bunch of cute otters
over there. I want one! Ow!

1:14:25.632 --> 1:14:27.092
Ow, Bailey!

1:14:27.176 --> 1:14:29.256
Oh! I see the truck. It's over there.

1:14:29.428 --> 1:14:31.098
-Okay, what would dory do?
-I don't see how we can get on it.

1:14:31.263 --> 1:14:33.263
Oh, man, if only there was a way
to stop traffic.

1:14:33.432 --> 1:14:36.022
Stop traffic. Stop traffic!
Everyone needs to stop.

1:14:36.185 --> 1:14:38.355
People stop to look at things. Things
that they like. Things that are cute.

1:14:38.854 --> 1:14:41.864
Things that are cute! Okay, I got it.

1:14:41.899 --> 1:14:43.609
-What? What is it?
-Quickly before I forget.

1:14:43.775 --> 1:14:46.395
Destiny, when the truck reaches
the bridge you flip me up there.

1:14:46.570 --> 1:14:47.150
Got it.

1:14:47.279 --> 1:14:50.069
You guys, follow me.
Everyone else, stay here.

1:14:50.240 --> 1:14:53.790
Whoa. Dory.
Honey, you're not leaving us again.

1:14:53.952 --> 1:14:55.622
Your mother's right.
You have to stay with us.

1:14:55.787 --> 1:14:59.617
Dory, what happens if--
you know, if you're gone for too long.

1:14:59.791 --> 1:15:02.501
And what if you get confused and that
