1:17:01.747 --> 1:17:06.537
We need to go back. Becky, back!
Back, Becky! Loo-loo. Ooo-roo-roo.

1:17:07.211 --> 1:17:08.881
-Please don't eat us!
-Where's dory?

1:17:09.046 --> 1:17:10.666
-Who are you?
-Jenny?

1:17:10.797 --> 1:17:12.007
-Marlin?
-Charlie?

1:17:12.090 --> 1:17:16.010
-Nemo? Thank you so much.
-Thank you for taking care of dory.

1:17:16.178 --> 1:17:18.098
Dory! She's still in the truck.

1:17:18.263 --> 1:17:22.063
Becky! Fetch dory! Ooo-roo. Dor-roo.

1:17:25.521 --> 1:17:27.731
Okay, kid. I guess this is goodbye.

1:17:27.856 --> 1:17:29.066
-No!
-What do you mean, "no"?

1:17:29.233 --> 1:17:31.743
You're not going to the Cleveland.
You are coming to the ocean with me.

1:17:31.777 --> 1:17:33.397
What is it with you
and ruining my plans?

1:17:33.487 --> 1:17:36.567
Listen to me, I have one goal in life.
One! And it is to--

1:17:36.740 --> 1:17:40.410
no, you listen to me. What is so great
about plans? I never had a plan.

1:17:40.452 --> 1:17:44.042
Did I plan to lose my parents? No.
Did I plan to find marlin? No.

1:17:44.206 --> 1:17:46.826
Did you and I plan to meet?
Wait. Did we?

1:17:46.959 --> 1:17:49.129
-Are you almost done?
-Well, I don't think we did.

1:17:49.253 --> 1:17:52.093
And that's because the best things
happen by chance. Because that's life.

1:17:52.256 --> 1:17:56.796
That's you being with me out
in the ocean not safe in some glass box.

1:17:56.969 --> 1:17:57.969
-Can I say something?
-I'm not done!

1:17:58.095 --> 1:18:01.265
A friend of mine-- her name's
sigourney-- once told me that...

1:18:01.431 --> 1:18:02.931
All it takes is three simple steps:

1:18:03.100 --> 1:18:06.480
Rescue, rehabilitation,
and one other thing--

1:18:06.645 --> 1:18:07.735
release!

1:18:08.772 --> 1:18:10.942
That's right! So what do you say?

1:18:11.108 --> 1:18:14.068
Release! Release! Release!

1:18:14.236 --> 1:18:17.526
Release! Release! Release!

1:18:17.656 --> 1:18:20.236
Release! Release! Release!

1:18:20.284 --> 1:18:21.794
I was gonna say, "okay."

1:18:24.162 --> 1:18:25.462
Not good.

1:18:25.789 --> 1:18:27.789
-Oh no! They're going away!
-Oh no! Dory! What do we do?

1:18:27.916 --> 1:18:29.456
Quick! Guys, grab my fin!

1:18:31.587 --> 1:18:35.337
Ooh! He's trying to get the door open.
Ooh. It's locked from the outside.

1:18:35.424 --> 1:18:36.634
Come on, dory. You can do it.

1:18:36.800 --> 1:18:39.140
Destiny! Destiny! Wall! Wall! Wall!

1:18:40.470 --> 1:18:43.010
-Dory, no! Wait!
-Dory!

1:18:43.682 --> 1:18:47.192
-Bailey, where are they headed?
-Ooh. I'm losing them.

1:18:51.607 --> 1:18:53.567
Dory, it's over.

1:18:53.817 --> 1:18:56.817
-No, there's got to be a way.
-Yeah. There's a way!

1:18:56.987 --> 1:18:59.607
Dory, now listen to me.
There's no way to get out.

1:18:59.781 --> 1:19:02.121
But-- there's got to be a way.
There's always a way.

1:19:02.701 --> 1:19:05.831
There isn't, dory. I'm telling you.
This time there is no other way.

1:19:06.038 --> 1:19:07.408
Well, what about that?

1:19:09.708 --> 1:19:11.498
Holy carp. There is another way.

1:19:12.544 --> 1:19:14.094
Take a deep breath, kid.

1:19:14.213 --> 1:19:16.513
Release! Release! Release!

1:19:16.673 --> 1:19:20.683
Release! Release! Release! Release!

1:19:25.849 --> 1:19:28.889
-What is that?
-I don’t care what it is! Get it off!

1:19:29.019 --> 1:19:30.439
What the--

1:19:30.896 --> 1:19:32.356
suck it, bipeds.

1:19:33.524 --> 1:19:36.784
All right, Hank, you've got seven arms--
i don't know. Just try something.

1:19:36.902 --> 1:19:38.152
Okay. Here we go.

1:19:39.988 --> 1:19:43.528
-Huh? Hey! Stop. Stop. Wait! No!
-Hey! Hey! Stop. Wait. Oh no!

1:19:43.617 --> 1:19:46.367
-That's doing something.
-And we are moving. Good job, Hank.

1:19:46.495 --> 1:19:51.465
-Wait, wait, wait! Come on! Whoa!
-Hey! What? Hey! Stop! Wait. Wait.

1:19:51.583 --> 1:19:54.883
Listen, I'm not trying to tell you
how to drive. Certainly I can't do--

1:19:55.045 --> 1:19:56.705
I'm not in any position--
but could you go faster?

1:19:56.880 --> 1:19:59.880
No! No, no! No, no, no!

1:20:02.344 --> 1:20:04.514
-Whoo!
-Hey! Give us our truck back!

1:20:04.638 --> 1:20:06.218
I can't see squat.
Which way are we going?

1:20:06.390 --> 1:20:10.310
Okay. Well, all the cars
are going left so go left.

1:20:10.435 --> 1:20:13.895
Gilman street. Ashby Avenue. Powell.

1:20:13.939 --> 1:20:16.519
Gilman street again. Huh.
Gilman street again.

1:20:16.567 --> 1:20:18.527
How much longer
are we gonna veer left?

1:20:21.405 --> 1:20:23.955
Okay, we just need to know
how we got on,

1:20:24.032 --> 1:20:25.372
then we'll know how to get off.

1:20:25.492 --> 1:20:27.042
Well, let me know
when you figure it out.

1:20:27.160 --> 1:20:28.750
Unfortunately I can't remember
how we got on.

1:20:28.912 --> 1:20:31.252
Hey, I know those guys!
That's where we came from. Turn right.

1:20:31.331 --> 1:20:32.831
Here we go!

1:20:37.713 --> 1:20:42.093
-Hey! Hey, hey, hey! Wait!
-Oh my-- whoa. Hey!

1:20:42.593 --> 1:20:44.723
We are so fired.

1:20:44.970 --> 1:20:49.350
Keep straight. Straight. Left. Left.
No, no, no. Right. Right. Right.

1:20:50.434 --> 1:20:52.524
-Good driving, Hank.
-Pay attention to the road.

1:20:52.644 --> 1:20:54.904
Oh, I'm sorry. Oh. Uh-oh.
Fork in the road.

1:20:55.022 --> 1:20:57.402
-Which way?
-Ocean. Ocean. Hey, a boat!

1:20:57.524 --> 1:20:59.364
You know, I haven't had
great experiences with boats, but i--

1:20:59.484 --> 1:21:02.954
-which way?
-Boats go to the ocean. Right!

1:21:02.988 --> 1:21:04.278
Hold on!

1:21:07.534 --> 1:21:08.704
We're out of time, kid.
Where do we go now?

1:21:08.827 --> 1:21:11.957
Okay, I'll figure it out.
I don't know, but--

1:21:12.039 --> 1:21:13.289
well, something will come and--

1:21:14.791 --> 1:21:18.841
seagulls. Hank, follow those birds!
The ocean's left, Hank.

1:21:20.047 --> 1:21:22.257
Mine, mine, mine, mine.

1:21:22.299 --> 1:21:25.219
Ooh. Hold on. Ooh.
I'm getting something.

1:21:25.302 --> 1:21:26.642
Is it them? Is everything perfect?

1:21:26.803 --> 1:21:30.313
Uh-oh, it's the fuzz. Busted.

1:21:33.852 --> 1:21:37.312
Okay, we're good. The ocean!
It's straight ahead. Floor it!

1:21:37.481 --> 1:21:38.441
Now we're talking.

1:21:40.150 --> 1:21:43.150
-Oh. Uh-oh!
-What do you mean, "uh-oh"?

1:21:43.237 --> 1:21:45.697
Oh no. What would I do?
What would I do? What would I do?

1:21:46.698 --> 1:21:49.078
Hank, I'm gonna ask you
to do something crazy.

1:21:49.201 --> 1:21:50.871
I'm okay with crazy.

1:21:51.578 --> 1:21:52.788
All right, Hank.

1:21:52.913 --> 1:21:56.963
Ooh. There's no way out. It's over.
They're going to fish jail! Ooh!

1:21:57.125 --> 1:22:02.125
Wait. Ooh. Oh no. Ooh.
Get back! Incoming!

1:22:34.663 --> 1:22:37.713
Fish!

1:22:44.131 --> 1:22:48.391
What lies before you represents
the third and final part of the...

1:22:48.719 --> 1:22:50.349
Marine life mission.

1:22:50.512 --> 1:22:55.682
Rescue, rehabilitation, and release.

1:22:56.435 --> 1:22:58.235
Come to papa.

1:23:03.859 --> 1:23:07.069
I'm sigourney Weaver.
Thank you for joining me.

1:23:10.073 --> 1:23:13.873
One, two, three, four...

1:23:15.913 --> 1:23:18.833
Wait a minute. Why am I counting?
Hey, where is everyone?

1:23:18.957 --> 1:23:23.207
Uh-oh, did they leave me? No! No, no.
They wouldn't do that.

1:23:23.378 --> 1:23:26.258
Okay. That's okay. I can figure this out.
What was I just doing then?

1:23:26.423 --> 1:23:30.433
I was covering my face,
so I was trying to hide.

1:23:30.594 --> 1:23:32.764
Okay, so why was I trying to hide? Wait!

1:23:32.930 --> 1:23:34.760
Oh, i-- five, six, seven, eight,
nine, ten.

1:23:34.848 --> 1:23:36.308
Ready or not, here I come!

1:23:36.433 --> 1:23:37.773
Ha, found you!

1:23:37.935 --> 1:23:38.775
I see you!

1:23:38.894 --> 1:23:39.984
Haha! Gotcha!

1:23:40.145 --> 1:23:42.105
All right, you little shrimps,
recess is over.

1:23:42.272 --> 1:23:44.442
-Aw, man.
-Ah, nobody found me!

1:23:44.608 --> 1:23:46.528
Bring it in. Time for another--

1:23:46.610 --> 1:23:48.150
don't touch me.
Time for another lesson.

1:23:48.320 --> 1:23:50.820
When is Mr. ray coming back
from his migration?

1:23:50.989 --> 1:23:53.119
If he's smart he'll stay away from here
as long as he can.

1:23:53.283 --> 1:23:55.123
